      "id": "PopularPost22656",
      "post_content": "Not an absolute staple counter, but very close. First off, it's one of the only absolute unconditional counters for 1U, which does in fact make the spell go to the graveyard. Secondly, some decks don't particularly care much if they lose a bit of card advantage. Thirdly, the aforementioned decks may also greatly benefit from their own card advantage. And lastly, your opponent may legally forget to draw the cards -- it is a choice for them, not a forced draw. ",
